Forewing length 65.1-80.6 mm (average 74.1 mm, n = 3). Color of body and wings similar to male (Figs 2, 3). Mandible with base dark reddish-brown, rest blackish; shape similar to 
Corydalus nubilus
Erichson and 
Corydalus crossi
, basal preapical tooth moderately separated from second (Fig. 8; 
Contreras-Ramos 1998, fig. 27I
; 
Contreras-Ramos 2002, fig. 27
). Antenna filiform, pale brown.

Key to long-mandibled males of known Corydalus species from Venezuela (modified from 
Contreras-Ramos 2002
